animations living matter lab living matter lab home people research teaching publications movies animations activities animation a challenge in developing educational materials related to human anatomy is figuring out how best to visually represent organs in the body this project explores the potential of computational models as tools for education about the human cardiovascular system the interactive animation depicts blood flow during a complete cardiac cycle the motion of the ventricles is based upon a finite element analysis of fully coupled electromechanical behavior of cardiac tissue while vector illustrations add context to show the path of a cell through the heart by combining computational models with interactive animation we aim show the human heart in a way that is both mechanically realistic and visually engaging retrieved from http biomechanics stanford edu cgi bin index php title animations&oldid 3207 member login log in page discussion view source history what links here recent changes upload file special pages
